Parliament, Monday, 17 May 2021 – The Portfolio Committee on Higher Education, Science and Technology will tomorrow undertake an oversight visit to the NSFAS Head Office to engage with the newly appointed board and management on their plans and strategy for the scheme.
	
	As part of the oversight visit, the committee will conduct site visits to the facilities within the entity to monitor the administration and disbursement of funding and allowances to students at universities and TVET colleges.
	
	Details of the oversight are as follows:
	Date: Tuesday, 18 May 2021
	Time: 09:00
	Venue: 2nd floor, House of Vincent, 10 Brodie Road, Wynberg
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES 
	
